video-based-steganography
Tkinter GUI tool for hiding and extracting text data within video files.

Features:

Encode: Hide text data within selected video.
Decode: Extract hidden text from video.
Displays original and decoded video information (size, width, height).
Usage:

Run the Python script.
Click "Encode" to hide text within an video.
Click "Decode" to extract hidden text from an video.
Follow on-screen instructions to select video and input text.

Dependencies:
Python 3.12
Tkinter
PIL (Python Imaging Library)
To Run: py -3.12 c:\Users\jalal\OneDrive\Desktop\vid_stego_app.py

Ensure Python is installed on your system.
Install required dependencies using pip if not already installed (pip install pillow).
Run the Python script using VS code
